 "progression_beyond": "11th-level Patriarch: 4,4,4,3,3 spells; 12th: fours across the board; 13th: 5,5,5,4,4; and so on.",
 "description": "Part fighter, part mage: magic armor and all non-edged magic weapons (no arrows!), more usable items than the fighter, and spells of their own from 2nd level. A Patriarch who builds a stronghold receives help from above — construction at double value per Gold Piece — and fanatically loyal faithful troops at no cost: 10-60 heavy cavalry, 10-60 horsed crossbowmen, 30-180 heavy foot. Clerics are of Law or of Chaos, sharply divided; a Patriarch who changes sides forfeits every benefit at once. Cleric castles rule a territory like a Barony, tithed at 20 GP per inhabitant per year. Anti-Clerics of Chaos work the reversed forms of the underlined spells.",
 "special_notes": [
